notesStmt.note: Damp entry at head and tail.
Mould darkening and losses at end.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.textLang: Hebrew; Jewish Babylonian Aramaic (ca. 200-1200 CE); Arabic

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 25; written lines: 25; Uniform layout. Catchwords on every verso. Titles and inital words in larger square characters. Marginal notes.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental (Persian?) semi-cursive and square script of the 14th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Brown leather, blind tooled, with leather ties. Boxed. Spine: 'Zachariah ben Judah Aghmati. Commentary on Talmud. Hebrew-Aramaic. Vol. I. Brit. Mus. Oriental 11,361.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Dr A. Freimann: purchased from him by the British Museum on 12 November 1932: inscribed, folio [189v].
